title: For Sale/Trade:  Blueprinted Remington 700 - 6.5 Creedmoor
postcontent:
For your consideration is a blueprinted Remington 700 chambered in 6.5 Creedmoor.  The action has been squared and trued center to bore; the inner tenon was opened up .010" and new threads were single point cut center to bore. The actions lugs have also been squared and trued. The bolt lugs, as well as the bolt nose and face have been trued and squared. All machine work is done on a precision lathe with a single point cuter all center to bore. Both the action and bolt are dial indicated to .0001" before any work is performed.

A brand new Shilen, match grade, chrome barrel was used for this custom build. The contour is a sendero contour (sometimes called the Rem varmint), 8 twist and finished at 26". The barrel threads were also single point cut and hand fit to this action. The breech was cut to .0035" and the headspace was cut to .0015". This is much tighter than factory specs and will lead to a much more accurate shooter. The barrel was crowned with an 11 degree target crown.  I have the barreled action in a HS precision sendero stock with the BDL bottom metal.  The barrel has only 5 rounds through her... to test the chamber and put the rifle on paper.  I have plenty of pics to share showing the machine work being completed.

Once the machine work was completed and the rifle test fired the barreled action was caustic blued but can always be customized to your needs... Maybe add a muzzle brake; cerakote finish; detachable mag; Jewell trigger; custom paint the stock; ect.

The barreled action in a quality stock will easily shoot 3/4 MOA with factory ammo and is capable of 1/2 MOA or better using hand loaded ammo. I have a few other HS precision stocks and a few Bell and Carlson stocks to offer with this build if the HS stock is not to your liking.  Willing to sell just the barreled action for 1200 if you already have a stock and bottom metal.

I have a few other blueprinted Rem 700s available as well so if you have another caliber in mind send a note... I probably have it or can build it.

Will ship to your FFL if needed.

title: For Sale:  Customized Smith & Wesson M&P 45. Apex Trigger Kit, Night Sights, etc. Many Extras!
postcontent:
I have for sale a Customized Smith & Wesson M&P 45acp. I had some upgrades done to it: Apex (Machined Aluminum) Forward set sear and trigger kit (parts plus labor was $250) turns spoungy stock trigger into a match grade trigger with very little take up, about a 4lb pull weight and almost no overtravel also trigger is one piece instead of the factory hinged trigger which makes it much nicer to pull/shoot accurately, Stipple Job on front strap and backstrap of grip also the safety, mag release button and index points on both sides ($80), and Tru Dot "Night Sights" ($120), also barrel feed ramp was polished along with all internals, trigger guard was undercut and magwell flared. It comes with 2 factory mags a bottle of froglube and two boxes of Black Ops ammo 185gr. Also both mags are loaded with premium hollow points: Barnes tac-xp solid copper hp, and Winchester PDX 1's.
The only complaint with the Smith & Wesson line of pistols is the trigger. The factory trigger is spoungy and has ALOT of take up and reset and approx a 5lb pull weight. That has all been upgraded. I could sit here and Try to explain it but you really have to feel it for yourself.
I also still have all the parts for the factory trigger plus when the APEX trigger job was done I had to upgrade the sear housing block to the newest version so that's another new part. So if you have any questions please just let me know. I have roughly have $900 into it, and regrettably  I'll DROP THE PRICE and sell for $650. 

I also will throw in a complete set of:
 "David Tubbs" - AR15 - Chrome Silicone Steel Spring Kit. This is by far the best of the best spring kit for the AR15 rifle, actually it will fit any AR from a Cabine to a Rifle in terms of gas system lengths. All (Even the most expensive and high end brands and/or model) AR's (factory, Mil-Spec, Etc.) Use "MUSIC INSTRUMENT" wire spring steel in their guns. It is not the best that can be used, as a matter of fact the "music" quality spring steel Springs last approx 2000-5000 rounds until they fail. Obviously some before others depending on the specific spring in the gun. Usually the buffer spring or the extractor Springs are the first to fail due to the forces being applied to them more so than others. But this is where "Chrome Silicone Steel" Springs prevail. Personally I don't know why all high end guns don't use them. David Tubb designed a set of the most important springs that run an AR-15 rifle and did a lot of research before putting them to market. But a short explanation is: they are heat treated several times, shot peened, magnafluxed & inspected with ultraviolet light to detect any microscopic stress fractures that could lead to failure. So needless to say they did their homework and the proof is in the stats. Their springs last over 25,000 rounds and keep going. 
So if you have strictly a range toy then you can just rely on the factory music spring steel springs but if you're ever thinking you may need to use your AR to save a life or take one then I would want the best, because it's basically springs that run a gun. If even one breaks usually the gun is out of action until it's replaced. And who wants to try to try to fumble around in a hostile environment possibly low light, being shot at, Etc. while you're trying to change out a spring, and some of them cannot be changed out in the field at all. Like your ejector spring! If you don't believe me search around the web and see how often AR-15 "Extractor" springs fail. Do your own research, if I had a loved one who relied on an AR15 LE, Mil, Etc. I would buy them a set and send it to them. It's only about $80 shipped and all of the springs are easy enough to replace in minutes without any special tools, except maybe the ejector spring that one you need a roll punch but it's not too hard and not the most important spring in the kit. 
It consists of:  1 Extractor Spring, 1 Ejector Spring, 1 Buffer Spring (Flat Wound), 1 Hammer Spring, 1 Trigger Spring and 2 (Flat wound) 30rd. Magazine Springs.  So I'll throw in this set of NEW Springs that are still in the plastic sealed packaging, never used. I kept them for spares but had to sell my AR and realized I still have them but no use for them anymore. So I'll throw them in for a deal sweetener. I hope they can save a life!

PRICE DROP TO $650 
Thanks,
Nick - Phone#:
